comments: Okogie (MIN) moves laterally into LeVert's (IND) path and makes contact with his body, which affects his SQBR.
Sabonis (IND) brings his hand forward towards Towns (MIN) and marginal contact occurs as Towns secures the ball.
Holiday (IND) maintains a legal guarding position moving alongside Edwards (MIN) and absorbs the marginal contact during the drive.
During the drive, Sabonis (IND) momentarily places a resting hand on Towns' (MIN) front and the contact is marginal.

Towns (MIN) extends his arm out when he makes contact to Sabonis' (IND) face at the end of his drive. After communicating with the Replay Center it was determined the contact did not meet the criteria for a flagrant foul.
Russell (MIN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Sabonis (IND) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Okogie (MIN) legally contests LeVert's (IND) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Reid (MIN) extends his arms into Sabonis (IND) and dislodges him from his rebounding position.
Sabonis (IND) and Russell (MIN) tie each other up and a jump ball is correctly called.
Russell (MIN) brings his arm down to make contact with Sabonis' (IND) arm, which restricts his ability to tip the jump ball.
Reid (MIN) is already in McConnell's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
During the rebound, Sabonis (IND) pulls Reid's (MIN) jersey away from his body and the contact affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Brogdon (IND) does not bring part of his hand underneath the ball when he brings his dribble to a pause.
Holiday (IND) is progressing when he gathers the ball on his left foot and establishes his right as his pivot, which he maintains prior to releasing his dribble.
Okogie (MIN) is moving alongside Holiday's (IND) path and cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt.

Holiday (IND) gathers the ball and makes a basketball move towards the basket on his driving shot attempt. Any contact with Okogie's (MIN) face as he starts his upward shooting motion is deemed marginal.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
LeVert (IND) makes contact with Reid's (MIN) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
McConnell (IND) makes clean contact with the ball as he attempts to steal the ball from Russell (MIN) during the inbound.
Jackson (IND) commits a take foul on Russell (MIN).
Edwards (MIN) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to Indiana.
Prince (MIN) legally contests Holiday's (IND) jump shot attempt.
